      <scopecontent id="aspace_dc581927a121c09812e1bbfc97a96f4d">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Policy Sciences Center Records consist of organizational papers, correspondence, financial records, grant materials, and publications which document the founding of the Policy Sciences Center in 1948 and its activities over the next thirty years. The records are incomplete and primarily highlight the work of the association in the mid-1970s.</p>
         <p>The Policy Sciences Center Records were processed as part of a collaborative effort between Manuscripts and Archives and the Yale Law School to document the careers and accomplishments of law school faculty and alumni.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_2f4e3173e1e9689d1edadb630655d944">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Policy Sciences Center is a non-profit foundation incorporated in 1948 by Yale Law School faculty members Harold Lasswell, Myres McDougal, and George Dession. The broad mission of the Center was to improve the decision-making process by educating policy makers at all levels. It hosted topical seminars, provided a forum for discussion of topics ranging from juvenile justice to access to capital by minority groups, assisted interested parties in obtaining funds and expertise to perform research, and prepared and reviewed grant applications and reports.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_e15a22bbaad97cbe4873ed98619cbacc">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
